 Director Tomino: "There is a text I would like to introduce about what imagination is, Nobel Prize in Literature winner Mascara(?). Dr. Mascara (?), Nobel laureate in literature, said, 'Imaginative power is to imagine and express what is to come next. It is what creates new things. It is to abstract what has happened in the past and see what is essential, not to be obsessed with the concrete. In the process of exploring the unknown, if we see too much of the concrete, we will miss the unknown possibilities. Think of other possibilities with an open mind. The images are so thoroughly concrete that they lack the ability to see the essence. What you are making is a patchwork of past works! How dare you say, 'I won't understand unless you explain it to me?' Anyone who has ever said such a thing should quit!"
 
 He talks softly, but sometimes he is shouted at in a very loud voice. It's a bit of a nerve-wracking experience.
 
 Business is about never getting tired of doing it."
 
 Kierkegaard said, "Despair is a deadly disease."
 
 I'll post the rest later. I've got a bunch of stuff on Twitter, #sa09 and stuff like that.
